WHEREAS, Dolly Parton is one of our most beloved daughters, and through her
compassionate spirit and philanthropy, she has touched not only the lives of her fellow
Tennesseans, but also millions of lives around the world; and
WHEREAS, through Imagination Library, Dolly Parton has contributed greatly to
education and literacy by giving a truly great gift to thousands of children, a lifelong love of
reading; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we celebrate the thirtieth anniversary of Dolly Parton's Imagination Library,
a gift from the heart that continues to positively influence children the world over, and thank
Dolly Parton for this and her many other philanthropic contributions to society, paying tribute to
her generosity in helping others.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
